@NODE "Italiano" "Catalogo Italiano di ReOrg"

Requisiti:
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Sono necessari:

   - Amiga con sistema operativo 2.1 o superiore
   - ReOrg versione 3.11


Installazione:
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Purtroppo   (causa  pigrizia)  non ho  scritto un  programma  per l'ottimo
Installer della  Commodore.  Comunque non  dovrebbe essere  affatto difficile
installare questo catalogo; ma, se ci dovessere essere problemi, posso cerca-
re di spiegarmi:

1 - aprire una shell (quella finestra dove si può comunicare con Amiga impar-
    tendo comandi con la tastiera)
2 - modificare la directory corrente in quella che contiene il nuovo catalogo
    fornito; se,  per esempio,  l'archivio è stato  scompattato in `RAM:', si
    dovrebbe digitare:
       Cd RAM:ReOrg3.1/Catalogs/Italiano
3 - copiare il catalogo nella directory dei cataloghi; per esempio si potreb-
    be digitare:
       Copy ReOrg.catalog LOCALE:Italiano

   Ricordate che  si può memorizzare  il catalog assieme  al programma ReOrg,
avendo cura di copiarlo nella sottodirectory `Catalogs/Italiano'.

   @{" Un po di polemica " LINK "English" 26}

@ENDNODE


@NODE "English" "ReOrg Italian Catalog"
Requirements:
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   You will need:

   - an AmigaOS 2.1+
   - ReOrg v3.11


Installation:
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   I'm sorry. I did not write an Installer script (and I won't ever: I am too
lazy). However I think you will be  able to install this you by yourself, but
if you are not I will explain:

1 - open a shell
2 - change  the current  path to the  directory  containing  the catalog; for
    example, if you have unpacked to `RAM:', you should type
       Cd RAM:ReOrg3.1/Catalogs/Italiano
3 - copy the catalog to your catalogs' directory; for example you could type:
       Copy ReOrg.catalog LOCALE:Italiano

   Remember that it is  possible to store this  catalog in the directory that
contains ReOrg, if you store it in the subdirectory `Catalogs/Italiano'.


More Over:
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   This archive contains  the Italian catalog that  I've build and I use with
this powerful  program.  I'm VERY  disappointed  that, even  if this one does
support  localization,  the  shareware  package  (that you  could upload from
Aminet, for example)  hasn't got  neither a .cd file  (i.e. a Catalog Descri-
ptor) nor a  .ct file  (i.e. a Catalog  Translation).  This  way it is fairly
difficult for  the average  user (i.e. me  and, maybe, you)  to build his own
.catalog. I've been forced  to translate the German  catalog (... the English
one doesn't exist: it is built in :-).  Unfortunately I don't know German too
much (well,  I've heard  something like "ai,  svai, polizai",  but I think it
won't suffice :-). It was  a _very_hard_task_  looking at the german catalog,
while looking at the HEX  (and ASCII) display of  AZap v2.40 (thank you Denis
Gounelle for writing this one), and testing with ReOrg !
   Now I'm pretty sure it works and it works fine. I promise I will fix every
bug (better to be named  `bad translation') you  will find (obviously you are
supposed to send  a bug report to  me). However I hope  that the catalog will
be ok for you (... if you are Italian, and you use Italian catalogs).

Bye bye

   Alessandro Ponzio
   istrice@paola.dei.unipd.it
   istrice2@maya.dei.unipd.it
@ENDNODE
